Package org.dspace.app.xmlui.aspect.artifactbrowser

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CollectionViewer
    Display a single collection.
    CommunityBrowser
    Display a list of Communities and collections.
    CommunityBrowser.TreeNode
    Private class to represent the tree structure of communities and collections.
    CommunityViewer
    Display a single community.
    ConfigurableBrowse
    Implements all the browse functionality (browse by title, subject, authors, etc.) The types of browse available are configurable by the implementor.
    Contact
    Create a simple contact us page.
    FeedbackForm
    Display to the user a simple form letting the user give feedback.
    FeedbackSent
    Simple page to let the user know their feedback has been sent.
    FrontPageFeeds
    This simple component will add feed links.
    ItemRequestChangeStatusForm
    Display to the user a form to request change of permissions of a item.
    ItemRequestContactAuthor
    For 'helpdesk' to intervene and contact Item author/depositor for permission
    ItemRequestContactRequester
    Form for making initial contact with the requester
    ItemRequestForm
    Display to the user a simple form letting the user to request a protected item.
    ItemRequestResponseAction
    Original Concept, JSPUI version: Universidade do Minho at www.uminho.pt Sponsorship of XMLUI version: Instituto Oceanográfico de España at www.ieo.es
    ItemRequestResponseDecisionForm
    Display to the user a simple decision form to select sending or not a file to requester.
    ItemRequestResponseFalseForm
    Display to the user a simple form to send a message rejecting the file send.
    ItemRequestResponseSent
    Let admin/author know their email response has been sent
    ItemRequestResponseTrueForm
    Display to the user a simple form letting the user send a document with a message.
    ItemRequestSent
    Simple page to let the user know their mail and file has been sent.
    ItemRequestStatusChanged
    Display to the user a simple page to let the user know the mail to request change status of a item is sent.
    ItemViewer
    Display a single item.
    RestrictedItem
    Display an item restricted message.
    SendFeedbackAction  
    SendItemRequestAction
    This action will send a mail to request a item to administrator when all mandatory data is present.
    StatisticsViewer
    Transformer to display statistics data in XML UI.
